`template/` is the scaffold copied into new Rust projects that adopt this repo's linting, CI, and CTX-context tooling conventions. Depending on it means inheriting a fixed toolchain, a strict workspace-wide lint policy, and a CI pipeline that enforces both — plus the Claude Code hook wiring that keeps `.ctx` files current as the new project is edited.

The enforcement chain crosses several files and must stay consistent: `Cargo.toml`'s workspace lints are inert unless each member crate opts in with `[lints]\nworkspace = true`; `clippy.toml`'s hard-fail thresholds (80 lines, complexity 25) are a backstop for softer thresholds enforced externally by `scripts/rationale_check.py` and a planned dylint crate — change one only with the others in mind. `rust-toolchain.toml` pins the exact toolchain that `rustfmt.toml` assumes when claiming certain options are safely ignored on stable; bumping the toolchain requires re-verifying that assumption and re-running the full clippy restriction-lint list, since lint names shift across releases. `deny.toml` closes the dependency-supply-chain gap the lint configs don't cover (licenses, registries, duplicate/wildcard versions).

`scripts/ci.sh` is the single entry point that actually runs these checks (via `git ls-files`-based enumeration, never a filesystem walk) against a target repo; `install-tools.sh` is the one-time bootstrap that wires up the `ctx-*` binaries the `.claude/` hooks and `.gitattributes` merge driver depend on — until `ctx-regenerate` is implemented, `.ctx` merge conflicts must be resolved manually. `.github/` supplies the CI workflow that invokes `ci.sh`.

Two invariants span the whole subtree: `unsafe_code`, `unwrap`/`expect`/`panic`-family lints, and `#[allow(...)]` are all denied/forbidden with no per-crate override mechanism other than the narrow test-code exemptions in `clippy.toml`; and every enforcement layer here (lint config, CI script, dylint stand-ins) is explicitly provisional pending the real dylint rules described in `docs/DYLINT_RULES.md`.

No `intent.md` exists for this directory, so no divergence can be checked.